-- Ukraine hopes to unwind FX restrictions in next few months -c.bank
-- By William Schomberg
-- Wed Sep 03, 2014 05:14AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 3 (Reuters) - Ukraine expects to ease foreign exchange restrictions on foreign companies in the next few months, a central bank official said on Wednesday.

"We estimate we should be able to unwind these in the next few months," Aleksandr Pisaruk, first deputy head of Ukraine's central bank, told a Ukraine investment conference in London by videolink.